news.title: Anant Raj shares tumble 4% after launching QIP, sets floor price at ₹695.83
news.para: Shares of Anant Raj Ltd fell up to 4% on October 8 after the company’s board approved a qualified institutional placement (QIP) of equity shares with a floor price of Rs 695.83.. The move aims to raise capital efficiently in accordance with SEBI regulations. The stock has surged over 30% in the last month amid government plans for tax incentives for data centre developers and the company’s ambitious expansion plans.

news.title: Karnataka HC urges state government to frame plot guidelines
news.para: “The intent behind insertion of Section 17(2B) is to ensure that civic infrastructure and planned growth of towns are not compromised while also protecting the interests of innocent buyers,” the order stated.

news.title: Noida administration puts brakes on B&Bs operating from highrise flats
news.para: Noida district administration has issued notices to over 100 homeowners at Supernova towers for operating unregistered short-term rentals. Acting on complaints of nuisance and security risks, authorities are enforcing the Sarai Act, 1867, requiring properties offering hotel-like accommodations to register. This crackdown aims to regulate these operations and address concerns raised by residents.

news.title: Noida residents seek relief from demolition notices for extensions
news.para: Noida residents are pushing for the repeal of a state law that allows the Noida Authority to issue notices for minor home changes. Homeowners in several sectors have received notices for alterations like verandah glazing or backyard fencing. Residents argue these are practical improvements for security and weather protection, not major violations.

news.title: Panchkula’s colony rehabilitation plan fails to take off, awaits government nod
news.para: Panchkula Municipal Corporation's plans to regularize illegal colonies have stalled. Agendas approved six months ago are now defunct. Land ownership by Haryana Shehri Vikas Pradhikaran and the forest department means the MC lacks authority. Proposals for one-marla plots and basic facilities in colonies like Indira, Rajiv, and Manav Colony have been rejected or require external approval.

news.title: Telangana RERA slaps fines on Bhuvanteza Infra, orders refunds to customers
news.para: Telangana Real Estate Regulatory Authority has fined Bhuvanteza Infra Projects Pvt. Ltd. 6.4 lakh. The authority ordered the company to refund buyers in three cases. These cases involved unregistered and delayed housing projects. Buyers paid significant amounts for flats. The company failed to deliver possession. TGRERA directed refunds with interest. This action protects homebuyers from builder misconduct.

news.title: Delhi: 4,000 society members hold protest march, want auction of land halted
news.para: Over 4,000 Revanta Multi State CGHS Ltd Society members marched to the DM South West office. They demanded a halt to the auction of their land. The land was procured for constructing flats. A Rera court ordered the sale. Members claim other society members were not heard. The sub-district magistrate assured cooperation.

news.title: Lodha Developers records 7% rise in July-September pre-sales at ₹4,570 crore
news.para: Lodha Developers announced strong financial results for the September quarter. Pre-sales saw a 7% increase year-on-year, reaching Rs 4,570 crore. Collections also grew by 13% to Rs 3,480 crore. For the first half of the financial year, pre-sales stood at Rs 9,020 crore, an 8% rise. The company is on track to meet its future sales targets.

news.title: Ashtech Group to invest ₹1,800 crore to develop residential project in Greater Noida West
news.para: Ashtech Group has entered the real estate sector with a significant investment of ₹1,800 crore in a new housing project in Greater Noida West. The development will be situated on a 5.6-acre plot, acquired for approximately ₹300 crore. This move marks the group's expansion into property development, leveraging their expertise from allied sectors.

news.title: House prices in Britain rise by 1.3% in September 2025: Halifax
news.para: British house prices saw a slower-than-expected 1.3% annual increase to September, marking the weakest rise since April 2024. Prices also unexpectedly fell by 0.3% month-on-month, with economic and tax uncertainty impacting the market. Despite this, modest growth is anticipated for the remainder of the year.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves slum cluster redevelopment scheme for Mumbai
news.para: The Maharashtra Cabinet has approved a scheme to redevelop Mumbai's slums into integrated housing projects, aiming to improve living conditions and urban infrastructure. Additionally, a state-wide sewage treatment and reuse policy was greenlit to promote a circular economy and sustainable urban growth.

news.title: Parsvnath Developers, Unity Group lease entire three lakh sq ft retail space at upcoming Delhi mall
news.para: Parsvnath Developers and Unity Group have fully leased the 3 lakh sq ft retail space in their joint shopping mall, 'Unity One Elegante', at Netaji Subhash Place, Delhi. The Occupancy-Cum-Completion Certificate has been received, and the mall is set to open soon. This development marks a significant step for the joint venture.

news.title: Auro Realty eyes $225 million India bond issue to fund acquisition
news.para: Auro Realty, the real estate arm of Aurobindo Group, plans to raise 20 billion rupees via bond sales to fund a significant acquisition, including Hotel Taj Banjara Hyderabad. The company is set to issue two- and four-year bonds with coupons between 11% and 15%, with private credit funds expected to invest.

news.title: Keystone Realtors' sales bookings rises 9% to ₹763 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Keystone Realtors reported a 9% year-on-year increase in sales bookings for the second quarter of FY26, reaching Rs 763 crore. This growth was driven by improved property demand. For the first six months of the fiscal year, sales bookings surged by 40% to Rs 1,831 crore.

news.title: WeWork India IPO sails through on last day; subscribed 1.15 times
news.para: WeWork India's initial public offer successfully concluded, achieving 1.15 times subscription, primarily driven by institutional buyers. The Rs 3,000-crore offer for sale saw strong interest from Qualified Institutional Buyers, while retail and non-institutional investor portions were undersubscribed. The listing aims to enhance visibility and provide liquidity for existing shareholders.

news.title: Tamil Nadu allocates ₹1.2 crore for Thiruverumbur Sipcot industrial park development
news.para: The Tamil Nadu government has allocated Rs 1.2 crore for road and water infrastructure development at Thiruverumbur Sipcot industrial park in Trichy. The 125-acre park, located near the Trichy Semi-ring Road, is slated to be fully allocated to a major electronics industry investor. Sipcot aims to secure this investment by January 2026.

news.title: ED attaches 34 more properties worth over ₹40 crore in MUDA scam case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has attached 34 more properties valued at over Rs 40 crore in the Mysore Urban Development Authority (MUDA) land scam case, bringing the total to over Rs 440 crore.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-Heritage plans drone surveillance for violations
news.para: Jaipur Municipal Corporation-Heritage is set to deploy drones for surveillance of unauthorized construction and building bylaw violations in the Walled City. Regular drone flights will also monitor issues like stray cattle and sewer blockages. The corporation is currently evaluating drone companies through demonstrations before a final decision on feasibility and budget.

news.title: Mauda police crack down on illegal sand mining, case registered
news.para: Mauda police acted on a tip-off and raided an illegal sand mining site in Chikhalbodi. Authorities seized a tractor and a trolley full of sand. Sanket Petkule was apprehended at the scene. A case has been registered against him under relevant acts. The police are continuing their efforts to stop illegal sand mining in the area.

news.title: Varmora Granito promoters buy back 2% stake from Carlyle Group
news.para: Varmora Granito promoters have bought back a 2% stake from private equity investor Carlyle Group. This move signals confidence ahead of the company's upcoming public offering. The promoters repurchased the stake for ₹100 crore. Varmora Granito is preparing for a 100% book-built initial public offering. The company plans to use fresh issue proceeds to reduce debt.
